# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorPath1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "The battlements fell quickly as the rest of the vanguard's soldiers made their way up the ladder."
    new "The battlements fell quickly as the rest of the vanguard's soldiers made their way up the ladder."

    old "Only a handful had died ascending the ladders, and for those deaths the Bagrad soldiers atop the battlements were made to pay dearly."
    new "Only a handful had died ascending the ladders, and for those deaths the Bagrad soldiers atop the battlements were made to pay dearly."

    old "Sarah watched their morale break nearly instantly as the first wave of soldiers made it onto the walls."
    new "Sarah watched their morale break nearly instantly as the first wave of soldiers made it onto the walls."

    old "Some stayed, throwing their life away for a battle that seemed already lost. Most dropped their weapons and began to run."
    new "Some stayed, throwing their life away for a battle that seemed already lost. Most dropped their weapons and began to run."

    old "She saw an arrow catch one of the soldiers in the back, collapsing to the ground. His comrades trampled over him."
    new "She saw an arrow catch one of the soldiers in the back, collapsing to the ground. His comrades trampled over him."

    old "They would keep running, throw away their armor, their weapons, run back to their homes and pretend to be citizens."
    new "They would keep running, throw away their armor, their weapons, run back to their homes and pretend to be citizens."

    old "Better that than a violent death, Sarah thought."
    new "Better that than a violent death, Sarah thought."

    old "She wasn't the young girl she'd been when she first fled her homeland. She had blood on her hand as much as any other in the mercenary company."
    new "She wasn't the young girl she'd been when she first fled her homeland. She had blood on her hand as much as any other in the mercenary company."

    old "And yet, she had never managed to learn to love the carnage in the way that some could."
    new "And yet, she had never managed to learn to love the carnage in the way that some could."

    old "Each death still haunted her."
    new "Each death still haunted her."

    old "Despite this, she also knew she could not yield. Her heart had been steeled a long time ago when she first set upon this path."
    new "Despite this, she also knew she could not yield. Her heart had been steeled a long time ago when she first set upon this path."

    old "She had known the killing that would come, and she had accepted that bargain long ago."
    new "She had known the killing that would come, and she had accepted that bargain long ago."

    old "Gather up!"
    new "Gather up!"

    old "Sarah declared as she stepped down from the final flights of the stairs that led down from the great walls into the streets of Bagrad."
    new "Sarah declared as she stepped down from the final flights of the stairs that led down from the great walls into the streets of Bagrad."

    old "A small cadre of soldiers followed in her footsteps."
    new "A small cadre of soldiers followed in her footsteps."

    old "Sarah had studied the maps of the city, but down at the street level, it was harder to make sense of where they were."
    new "Sarah had studied the maps of the city, but down at the street level, it was harder to make sense of where they were."

    old "Still, she knew roughly where the palace stood, which was enough."
    new "Still, she knew roughly where the palace stood, which was enough."

    old "Our only chance is if we keep our momentum!"
    new "Our only chance is if we keep our momentum!"

    old "You straggle, you get left behind."
    new "You straggle, you get left behind."

    old "The soldiers battered their swords against their shields, acknowledging her words."
    new "The soldiers battered their swords against their shields, acknowledging her words."

    old "First one in the palace gets double their share of the loot!"
    new "First one in the palace gets double their share of the loot!"

    old "To this, she received an approving cheer."
    new "To this, she received an approving cheer."

    old "Leading her unit, Sarah started to jog at a moderate pace."
    new "Leading her unit, Sarah started to jog at a moderate pace."

    old "They had to make time, but Sarah also knew that the city and its many tall buildings offered countless chances of an ambush."
    new "They had to make time, but Sarah also knew that the city and its many tall buildings offered countless chances of an ambush."

    old "As she began making her way through the city, she could see the windows of the houses were battened down."
    new "As she began making her way through the city, she could see the windows of the houses were battened down."

    old "The make-shift barricades would prove no obstacle to the armies that would soon descend on the city, and still the citizens had put them up."
    new "The make-shift barricades would prove no obstacle to the armies that would soon descend on the city, and still the citizens had put them up."

    old "It offered them safety, if only the illusion of it."
    new "It offered them safety, if only the illusion of it."

    old "Other than that, she found the city to be a ghastly place. It's size belied the fact that most of it was empty."
    new "Other than that, she found the city to be a ghastly place. It's size belied the fact that most of it was empty."

    old "Some of it deserted in anticipation of their arrival, but much more of it deserted far before then."
    new "Some of it deserted in anticipation of their arrival, but much more of it deserted far before then."

    old "This was what it felt like to walk the streets of a dead city. To walk streets and squares build to hosts tens-of-thousands, now emptied out."
    new "This was what it felt like to walk the streets of a dead city. To walk streets and squares build to hosts tens-of-thousands, now emptied out."

    old "It was after nearly half-an-hour of marching that they met any opposition at all."
    new "It was after nearly half-an-hour of marching that they met any opposition at all."

    old "Coming upon an open city square, dominated by a large fountain which had long run dry, Sarah spotted a small unit of Bagrad soldiers."
    new "Coming upon an open city square, dominated by a large fountain which had long run dry, Sarah spotted a small unit of Bagrad soldiers."

    old "All in all, it couldn't have been more than a dozen soldiers, each in a state of unpreparedness, still putting on their armor and sharpening their blades."
    new "All in all, it couldn't have been more than a dozen soldiers, each in a state of unpreparedness, still putting on their armor and sharpening their blades."

    old "Too late for that, Sarah thought."
    new "Too late for that, Sarah thought."

    old "Charge!"
    new "Charge!"

    old "Her command sent her own unit of soldiers rushing forward."
    new "Her command sent her own unit of soldiers rushing forward."

    old "Outnumbering them by a solid margin and already hyped by the start of battle, Sarah knew instantly that this was no real fight."
    new "Outnumbering them by a solid margin and already hyped by the start of battle, Sarah knew instantly that this was no real fight."

    old "Some of them scurried, but most of them simply stood in stunned silence."
    new "Some of them scurried, but most of them simply stood in stunned silence."

    old "Rushing up to them, Sarah came in close to a soldier. In his face, she could see only confusion. The last feeling he'd ever have."
    new "Rushing up to them, Sarah came in close to a soldier. In his face, she could see only confusion. The last feeling he'd ever have."

    old "She drove the blade through his shirt, into his heart."
    new "She drove the blade through his shirt, into his heart."

    old "Absent his armor, Sarah's blade cut right through him."
    new "Absent his armor, Sarah's blade cut right through him."

    old "She heard him gargle a sound, but only blood poured from his mouth."
    new "She heard him gargle a sound, but only blood poured from his mouth."

    old "He still looked confused as he stumbled back, Sarah's blade sliding out of his chest, now covered in a bright red."
    new "He still looked confused as he stumbled back, Sarah's blade sliding out of his chest, now covered in a bright red."

    old "All around her, she saw her soldiers rush up against the other Bagrad soldiers."
    new "All around her, she saw her soldiers rush up against the other Bagrad soldiers."

    old "Next to her, she saw a young Bagrad soldier, perhaps not even a man yet, fumbling for his sword."
    new "Next to her, she saw a young Bagrad soldier, perhaps not even a man yet, fumbling for his sword."

    old "Too late for that too, Sarah thought as she watched one of her men cut the boy down, slicing his neck open with the blade of an axe."
    new "Too late for that too, Sarah thought as she watched one of her men cut the boy down, slicing his neck open with the blade of an axe."

    old "As the last of the Bagrad soldiers fell around her, she saw three men running away."
    new "As the last of the Bagrad soldiers fell around her, she saw three men running away."

    old "Commander, should we give chase?"
    new "Commander, should we give chase?"

    old "Let them go. They're running away from the palace, no use wasting time trying to hunt them down."
    new "Let them go. They're running away from the palace, no use wasting time trying to hunt them down."

    old "Sarah raised up her blood-stained sword and pointed towards the palace."
    new "Sarah raised up her blood-stained sword and pointed towards the palace."

    old "Press on!"
    new "Press on!"

    old "Again, under her command, her soldiers advanced ever forward."
    new "Again, under her command, her soldiers advanced ever forward."

    old "Marching in the middle of her men, Sarah could feel the static in the air. Her senses growing deeper, more aware."
    new "Marching in the middle of her men, Sarah could feel the static in the air. Her senses growing deeper, more aware."

    old "It hadn't been the first time she'd felt it."
    new "It hadn't been the first time she'd felt it."

    old "Something always grew in the hearts of men in the middle of a battle. A kind of bloodlust, or perhaps survival instinct."
    new "Something always grew in the hearts of men in the middle of a battle. A kind of bloodlust, or perhaps survival instinct."

    old "The more they killed, the more they fought, the deeper they would sink into that primal version of themselves."
    new "The more they killed, the more they fought, the deeper they would sink into that primal version of themselves."

    old "The version that never cared for anything else, other than kill or be killed."
    new "The version that never cared for anything else, other than kill or be killed."

    old "Sarah held onto the feeling, but ever careful not to sink into it. She'd seen more than her share of brutality, carried out on a whim."
    new "Sarah held onto the feeling, but ever careful not to sink into it. She'd seen more than her share of brutality, carried out on a whim."

    old "You're still human. You're still a Rose."
    new "You're still human. You're still a Rose."

    old "Suddenly, the road before them opened up in all directions."
    new "Suddenly, the road before them opened up in all directions."

    old "Above her, the sky opened up, its light finally able to reach through and drive away the shade cast by the tall buildings."
    new "Above her, the sky opened up, its light finally able to reach through and drive away the shade cast by the tall buildings."

    old "The palace square."
    new "The palace square."

    old "Vast and open in a city otherwise drowned in buildings, it added to the majesty of the palace."
    new "Vast and open in a city otherwise drowned in buildings, it added to the majesty of the palace."

    old "The palace of Bagrad stood alone, surrounded by nothing, and reaching far up into the heavens, almost piercing the sky."
    new "The palace of Bagrad stood alone, surrounded by nothing, and reaching far up into the heavens, almost piercing the sky."

    old "For a moment, Sarah stood in awe of the monument. Then, a voice called out to her."
    new "For a moment, Sarah stood in awe of the monument. Then, a voice called out to her."

    old "Over here!"
    new "Over here!"

    old "Sarah turned away from the great building towards Kate's voice."
    new "Sarah turned away from the great building towards Kate's voice."

    old "She saw Kate running up to her, followed by another cadre of soldiers."
    new "She saw Kate running up to her, followed by another cadre of soldiers."

    old "She yelled out to her friend."
    new "She yelled out to her friend."

    old "They had been through a lot together, survived one battle after the other, and still Sarah worried the same each time for Kate."
    new "They had been through a lot together, survived one battle after the other, and still Sarah worried the same each time for Kate."

    old "What's the situation?"
    new "What's the situation?"

    old "We faced minimal resistance coming up on the palace. We arrived here just a bit before you."
    new "We faced minimal resistance coming up on the palace. We arrived here just a bit before you."

    old "What about the other units?"
    new "What about the other units?"

    old "Some are still making their way, but Sarah..."
    new "Some are still making their way, but Sarah..."

    old "Kate was hesitant with her words."
    new "Kate was hesitant with her words."

    old "Sarah didn't have patience."
    new "Sarah didn't have patience."

    old "What is it Kate, tell me."
    new "What is it Kate, tell me."

    old "The units lead by Caleb and Ephraim had arrived here first. They were waiting when we arrived and they...they've already went in."
    new "The units lead by Caleb and Ephraim had arrived here first. They were waiting when we arrived and they...they've already went in."

    old "Sarah cursed under her breath."
    new "Sarah cursed under her breath."

    old "They knew they had to wait here, to gather up all our strength before pressing into the palace."
    new "They knew they had to wait here, to gather up all our strength before pressing into the palace."

    old "I know. I told them as much, but they...they just didn't listen."
    new "I know. I told them as much, but they...they just didn't listen."

    old "Idiots. If they think they're going to get credit for going in first, despite my instructions, they'll have another thing coming."
    new "Idiots. If they think they're going to get credit for going in first, despite my instructions, they'll have another thing coming."

    old "So what do we do?"
    new "So what do we do?"

    old "If they went in by themselves, we should move up as well."
    new "If they went in by themselves, we should move up as well."

    old "We have most of the soldiers here now, the rest can catch up later."
    new "We have most of the soldiers here now, the rest can catch up later."

    old "I'm more worried that they've gotten themselves into trouble."
    new "I'm more worried that they've gotten themselves into trouble."

    old "Alright, you heard the commander! Rally up and get ready to move into the palace."
    new "Alright, you heard the commander! Rally up and get ready to move into the palace."

    old "Sarah watched as the soldiers fell into formation, taking this small moment of respite to prepare themselves for the next part."
    new "Sarah watched as the soldiers fell into formation, taking this small moment of respite to prepare themselves for the next part."

    old "Outside, Sarah could see no serious troop presence."
    new "Outside, Sarah could see no serious troop presence."

    old "A few faces lingered atop the towers of the castle, but Sarah couldn't even be certain they were soldiers. Perhaps simply scared civillians."
    new "A few faces lingered atop the towers of the castle, but Sarah couldn't even be certain they were soldiers. Perhaps simply scared civillians."

    old "Had Castle Reinmeer looked like this when the tribesmen pillaged her homeland?"
    new "Had Castle Reinmeer looked like this when the tribesmen pillaged her homeland?"

    old "Sarah raised her sword."
    new "Sarah raised her sword."

    old "Advance!"
    new "Advance!"

    old "Moving as one, the soldiers began a slow yet steady march up towards the palace."
    new "Moving as one, the soldiers began a slow yet steady march up towards the palace."

    old "Their heavy plated armor clattered with each step, causing their march to give off a dreadful rhythm."
    new "Their heavy plated armor clattered with each step, causing their march to give off a dreadful rhythm."

    old "Rising up on the steps to the palace, Sarah kept scanning the upper reaches. Waiting for an ambush that never came."
    new "Rising up on the steps to the palace, Sarah kept scanning the upper reaches. Waiting for an ambush that never came."

    old "Finally, her troops arrived at the great central gate and advanced into the palace."
    new "Finally, her troops arrived at the great central gate and advanced into the palace."

    old "Entering the palace, Sarah could feel the air instantly cool, covered from the scorching desert sun outside."
    new "Entering the palace, Sarah could feel the air instantly cool, covered from the scorching desert sun outside."

    old "In the distance, she saw a few people run. Servants, perhaps."
    new "In the distance, she saw a few people run. Servants, perhaps."

    old "Keep advancing down the hallway. The entrance to the western wing should be nearby."
    new "Keep advancing down the hallway. The entrance to the western wing should be nearby."

    old "Suddenly, screams rang out."
    new "Suddenly, screams rang out."

    old "The great halls of the palace converted the screams into nightmarish echoes."
    new "The great halls of the palace converted the screams into nightmarish echoes."

    old "Her troops? Sarah couldn't be sure."
    new "Her troops? Sarah couldn't be sure."

    old "Move up!"
    new "Move up!"

    old "The soldiers increased their pace, marching faster through the halls of the palace."
    new "The soldiers increased their pace, marching faster through the halls of the palace."

    old "As they drew nearer, Sarah could hear the screams grow louder and louder."
    new "As they drew nearer, Sarah could hear the screams grow louder and louder."

    old "A smell hit her nostrils, one sadly not unfamiliar to her."
    new "A smell hit her nostrils, one sadly not unfamiliar to her."

    old "Burning flesh."
    new "Burning flesh."

    old "Taking the lead, Sarah turned the corner and saw the source of the screams."
    new "Taking the lead, Sarah turned the corner and saw the source of the screams."

    old "A small ways off in the distance, nearer to the entrance of the western wing, Sarah could see her own soldiers, cowering behind pillars."
    new "A small ways off in the distance, nearer to the entrance of the western wing, Sarah could see her own soldiers, cowering behind pillars."

    old "All around them, deep ink black traces of soot were drawn across the floor and walls of the palace."
    new "All around them, deep ink black traces of soot were drawn across the floor and walls of the palace."

    old "A blinding light."
    new "A blinding light."

    old "Another set of screams."
    new "Another set of screams."

    old "Then, her eyes were drawn towards the object that hung in the center of the room, dominating all space around itself."
    new "Then, her eyes were drawn towards the object that hung in the center of the room, dominating all space around itself."

    old "Radiant, like a miniature sun, lashes of fire struck out and incinerated soldiers as though they were nothing."
    new "Radiant, like a miniature sun, lashes of fire struck out and incinerated soldiers as though they were nothing."

    old "Not an object, Sarah realized."
    new "Not an object, Sarah realized."

    old "A person."
    new "A person."

    old "In the midsts of the artifical sun, a man stood as if suspended in the air, defying any laws of nature."
    new "In the midsts of the artifical sun, a man stood as if suspended in the air, defying any laws of nature."

    old "His eyes burned like coals in a forge."
    new "His eyes burned like coals in a forge."

    old "It was impossible, and her mind screamed at the unnatural sight."
    new "It was impossible, and her mind screamed at the unnatural sight."

    old "It was impossible, except for one kind of person."
    new "It was impossible, except for one kind of person."

    old "A mage."
    new "A mage."

    old "Mage!"
    new "Mage!"

    old "Sarah screamed out the word and a bolt of panic ran through her soldiers."
    new "Sarah screamed out the word and a bolt of panic ran through her soldiers."

    old "Each of them was battle-hardened, had seen battles and bloodshed countless times over."
    new "Each of them was battle-hardened, had seen battles and bloodshed countless times over."

    old "They would charge into battle with song and drink themselves into a stupor to celebrate after."
    new "They would charge into battle with song and drink themselves into a stupor to celebrate after."

    old "But this was nothing like that."
    new "But this was nothing like that."

    old "Mages weren't like the rest of them, and their power far exceeded anything that a single soldier might bring."
    new "Mages weren't like the rest of them, and their power far exceeded anything that a single soldier might bring."

    old "Her men were ready to die on a battlefield face-to-face with the enemy, full of glory, but few among them could face something so unnatural."
    new "Her men were ready to die on a battlefield face-to-face with the enemy, full of glory, but few among them could face something so unnatural."

    old "Despite everything in her body telling her to retreat, Sarah knew there was only one way forward."
    new "Despite everything in her body telling her to retreat, Sarah knew there was only one way forward."

    old "Gathering up their morale, Sarah felt her soldiers move forward again, but she could sense their hesitation."
    new "Gathering up their morale, Sarah felt her soldiers move forward again, but she could sense their hesitation."

    old "Sarah saw Kate come up beside her."
    new "Sarah saw Kate come up beside her."

    old "Here, take this."
    new "Here, take this."

    old "Kate handed her a bow and arrow."
    new "Kate handed her a bow and arrow."

    old "Against a mage, the only reliable strategy was to run away. Since that was not an option, a bow and arrow was the least worst alternative."
    new "Against a mage, the only reliable strategy was to run away. Since that was not an option, a bow and arrow was the least worst alternative."

    old "As they drew nearer, Sarah could see the mage still hanging in the air, bringing down lashes of flame on any soldier that he could reach."
    new "As they drew nearer, Sarah could see the mage still hanging in the air, bringing down lashes of flame on any soldier that he could reach."

    old "With most of the soldiers hiding behind pillars, it meant his slaughter was a slow one, but it also meant there was no resistance left against him."
    new "With most of the soldiers hiding behind pillars, it meant his slaughter was a slow one, but it also meant there was no resistance left against him."

    old "Sarah could see the mage slowly drifting through the air, hunting down all those that remained."
    new "Sarah could see the mage slowly drifting through the air, hunting down all those that remained."

    old "Whenever he reached out, the flames swirled down on the soldiers, their screams filling up the hall."
    new "Whenever he reached out, the flames swirled down on the soldiers, their screams filling up the hall."

    old "Those that tried to run were swiftly burned as well."
    new "Those that tried to run were swiftly burned as well."

    old "They were trapped."
    new "They were trapped."

    old "As Sarah and her soldiers marched up closer, the sound of their stomping boots drew the mage's attention."
    new "As Sarah and her soldiers marched up closer, the sound of their stomping boots drew the mage's attention."

    old "He wheeled around in the air as if attached to a string."
    new "He wheeled around in the air as if attached to a string."

    old "Whatever held him up, if anything, Sarah couldn't see."
    new "Whatever held him up, if anything, Sarah couldn't see."

    old "His mouth opened, and a song drowned out all the other sound in the world."
    new "His mouth opened, and a song drowned out all the other sound in the world."

    old "He sang in a language that Sarah had never heard before, and whose every syllable struck her as if profoundly alien to anything she'd ever come across."
    new "He sang in a language that Sarah had never heard before, and whose every syllable struck her as if profoundly alien to anything she'd ever come across."

    old "Sarah felt the heat of the fire hit her before she turned and saw the bursting inferno."
    new "Sarah felt the heat of the fire hit her before she turned and saw the bursting inferno."

    old "A few rows over, some of her soldiers lit up, screaming their final words, their armors quickly melting against their bodies, trapping them inside them."
    new "A few rows over, some of her soldiers lit up, screaming their final words, their armors quickly melting against their bodies, trapping them inside them."

    old "Morale broke nearly instantly, their ranks scattering."
    new "Morale broke nearly instantly, their ranks scattering."

    old "Formations. Training. Morale. All of it was useless against a foe that could turn you to cinders simply by willing it so."
    new "Formations. Training. Morale. All of it was useless against a foe that could turn you to cinders simply by willing it so."

    old "Sarah closed her fist around the bow and arrow. It felt like a joke compared to what she was seeing."
    new "Sarah closed her fist around the bow and arrow. It felt like a joke compared to what she was seeing."

    old "Keep advancing!"
    new "Keep advancing!"

    old "She screamed, hoping at least some would gain courage from her words."
    new "She screamed, hoping at least some would gain courage from her words."

    old "Mages."
    new "Mages."

    old "Sarah had received limited instruction on dealing with them. People knew they were dangerous, exceedingly so, but they were also rare."
    new "Sarah had received limited instruction on dealing with them. People knew they were dangerous, exceedingly so, but they were also rare."

    old "She had spoken with seasoned soldiers who had never seen a mage in more than a decade of soldiering."
    new "She had spoken with seasoned soldiers who had never seen a mage in more than a decade of soldiering."

    old "Herself, she had only ever met a mage once when she was still little, perhaps only seven years old."
    new "Herself, she had only ever met a mage once when she was still little, perhaps only seven years old."

    old "Hiding behind her father, she had greeted the man who had a kind smile and a strange confident grace about him."
    new "Hiding behind her father, she had greeted the man who had a kind smile and a strange confident grace about him."

    old "Later, her father had told her that the man could have burned down their castle with ease, and that only a fool would ever mess with a mage."
    new "Later, her father had told her that the man could have burned down their castle with ease, and that only a fool would ever mess with a mage."

    old "Turns out I'm the fool, father."
    new "Turns out I'm the fool, father."

    old "Mages and their orders mostly kept to themselves, and so they rarely entered the field of battle, unless it served their interests."
    new "Mages and their orders mostly kept to themselves, and so they rarely entered the field of battle, unless it served their interests."

    old "Whatever his purpose here was, Sarah could hardly begin to speculate."
    new "Whatever his purpose here was, Sarah could hardly begin to speculate."

    old "It also didn't matter."
    new "It also didn't matter."

    old "He was an obstacle, between herself and her goal, and she'd deal with it like any other she had dealt with."
    new "He was an obstacle, between herself and her goal, and she'd deal with it like any other she had dealt with."

    old "Sarah kept pressing forward, only a handful of other soldiers continued along with her."
    new "Sarah kept pressing forward, only a handful of other soldiers continued along with her."

    old "From the corner of her eyes, she could see Kate was one of them. Kate, despite everything that had happened between them, was one of the few people she knew she could rely on."
    new "From the corner of her eyes, she could see Kate was one of them. Kate, despite everything that had happened between them, was one of the few people she knew she could rely on."

    old "Another soldier burst into flames, the heat exploding outward so violently, Sarah could feel it sear her face."
    new "Another soldier burst into flames, the heat exploding outward so violently, Sarah could feel it sear her face."

    old "Suddenly, the mage turned in the air. Away from Sarah and her soldiers."
    new "Suddenly, the mage turned in the air. Away from Sarah and her soldiers."

    old "For a moment, she felt grateful."
    new "For a moment, she felt grateful."

    old "You wanna fucking take someone on? How about you try me!"
    new "You wanna fucking take someone on? How about you try me!"

    old "Sarah watched as Caleb ran up from behind a pillar, aiming a crossbow up at the mage."
    new "Sarah watched as Caleb ran up from behind a pillar, aiming a crossbow up at the mage."

    old "A loud thumping sound rang out as the crossbow released the bolt."
    new "A loud thumping sound rang out as the crossbow released the bolt."

    old "In less than a fraction of second, the bolt crossed the distance and lodged itself..."
    new "In less than a fraction of second, the bolt crossed the distance and lodged itself..."

    old "In mid air."
    new "In mid air."

    old "Stunned, Sarah looked at the scene."
    new "Stunned, Sarah looked at the scene."

    old "It would have hit him, she thought. No, it should have hit him. The arc of the bolt was perfect, only to end up suspended in the air, inches from the mage's face."
    new "It would have hit him, she thought. No, it should have hit him. The arc of the bolt was perfect, only to end up suspended in the air, inches from the mage's face."

    old "The air itself shimmered around where the bolt was suspended, like ripples across the surface of water."
    new "The air itself shimmered around where the bolt was suspended, like ripples across the surface of water."

    old "The mage twisted his wrist."
    new "The mage twisted his wrist."

    old "Flames rose up around Caleb's feet."
    new "Flames rose up around Caleb's feet."

    old "Caleb!!!"
    new "Caleb!!!"

    old "Sarah heard Ephraim's screams."
    new "Sarah heard Ephraim's screams."

    old "She watched as Ephraim lunged for Caleb, tackling him."
    new "She watched as Ephraim lunged for Caleb, tackling him."

    old "Together the two tumbled across the stone floor. Only a fraction later did the ground erupt into flame, missing them by a hair."
    new "Together the two tumbled across the stone floor. Only a fraction later did the ground erupt into flame, missing them by a hair."

    old "We have to do something, Sarah told herself, commanding herself to press on."
